The President's put his faith in a man and appointed him to head the Agency's Foreign branch. This move follows a high-panel report on the SSA led by former minister Sydney Mufumadi. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former Ipid boss Robert McBride has a tough task cleaning up rogue elements within the State Security Agency while also working to increase its capability overseas. President Cyril Ramaphosa has put his faith in McBride by appointing him to head the Agency's foreign branch. READ: McBride to direct foreign branch of State Security Agency Former Foreign Intelligence Head Moe Shaik says it won't be easy for McBride and his team. "I would think that his first and almost immediate task would be to stabilise the organisation, to address the issue of low moral and to define the mission of the foreign branch of the SSA," said Shaik. 